	<div class="tuxIntro">
		<p>For those of you that don't know: Tux is the mascot of Linux, much like the Window logo is to Windows, and designer stubble is to Mac.</p>
		<p>Many versions of the Penguin exist on the internet, however the one shown on the right (taken from the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tux" target="blank">tux wikipedia page</a>) is the one that is generally agreed as the "official" one. Many prefer to make their own Tux logo's instead of using ones made by others. For a step by step guide of making your own Tux see my <a href="?page=Tutorials&sub=Tux">Tutorial</a>.</p>
		<p>Below is the gallery of Tux avatars I have created based off my original. Feel free to use as you wish, or send in links to your own and I can include them to help the community grow.</p>
	</div>
